# A file to hold the git hashes of commits that should be ignored when using git-blame.
# For each commit that is added it is suggested that a comment also be added about the
# purpose of the comment i.e. why it should be ignored.
# Each user needs to set this up locally in their copy of the repository using the
# command
#   git config blame.ignoreRevsFile .git-blame-ignore-revs
# This only needs to be done once.
